<div class="             ">
	<div class=" ">
		<h1>About Banner Network Southern Arizona</h1>
		<p>Banner Health is dedicated to making health care easier, so life can be better. This philosophy is at the heart of everything we do, even when it comes to introducing a new model for a physician network. We are excited to join with practices in Southern Arizona to carry out our mission to transform health care for the benefit of the communities we serve.</p>
<p><strong>Local physician leadership determines best practices for patient care</strong></p>
<p>We understand that local physicians know how to best care for their patients. Our network will be founded on a board structure that facilitates input to determine the best quality of care for patients and set standards of care for all to follow. Quality of care also influences the amount of any shared savings awarded to network practices. Local leadership is key to the success of the network.</p>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>A focus on coordination of care across the continuum</strong></p>
<p>Using a neighborhood model, we strongly encourage referrals to stay within the neighborhood. That makes it convenient for patients to get the additional care or tests they need to get an accurate, complete diagnosis. Primary care providers lead the team in care for their patients with results delivered in a timely manner through electronic health records.</p>
<p><strong>A dedicated support team for a successful practice</strong></p>
<p>Our independent providers do not have to go it alone. A team of caring experts will come alongside your practice to deliver specialized training and other information at your disposal. You&rsquo;ll have a team, including a medical director, provider relations, quality, coding and pharmacy, to support your practice and help you streamline workflows and improve efficiencies. Your team is available to assist you with any questions or issues that might be unique to your practice. Quarterly online meetings allow for additional training and timely updates on pressing issues and concerns.</p>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Technology tools that make patient care easier</strong></p>
<p>Working with partners like Innovaccer and Optum, Banner has adopted tools to make caring for patients easier and more efficient. For example, Innovaccer&rsquo;s InNote and InGraph tools give you a complete view of your patient while they are in your office, keeping records and documentation current. They work alongside your electronic health record platform to earn higher quality scores and increase the opportunity to earn shared savings.</p>
<p><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Demonstrated financial success in this quality-based payment model</strong></p>
<p>Using the Accountable Care Organization (ACO) model, Banner Health Network has delivered on the promise of high-quality care at a lower cost for more than 5 years. In 2019, BHN awarded $2.2 million in shared savings to network providers who qualified by achieving physician scorecard benchmarks.</p>
<p><strong>Community is at the heart of what we do</strong></p>
<p>Investing in the health of the communities we serve is part of our DNA. Not only in providing care to those in need, but also coming alongside nonprofits who are fulfilling special needs.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
    <li>In 2019, contributions by Banner Health had a community impact of $944 million in Tucson, including $10.6 million in charity care and financial assistance, $727,000 in community health service and $415,900 in community development.</li>
    <li>Banner University Health Plans (BUHP), part of the Banner Health Insurance Division located in Tucson, annually sponsors community events including Special Olympics Breakfast of Champions, NAMI Walks Southern Arizona, Tribal Opioid Conference, Dine Out for Safety (supporting Southern Arizona Center Against Sexual Assault) and Big Night Out in the Wild (supporting Big Brothers, Big Sisters).</li>
    <li>In addition, BUHP contributes more than $100,000 to local organizations to support services for the homeless, mental health services, veteran&rsquo;s services and assistance to foster children.</li>
    <li>Banner&rsquo;s Community Reinvestment Program recently awarded grants to 13 Southern Arizona nonprofits.</li>
</ul>
	</div>
</div>
